ktüren ermöglicht: von William Shakespeare über Don Giovanni und Virginia Woolf bis zu Gabriel Baur, der Regisseurin von »Venus Boyz« (2002).  afunded by »Transfer in der Lehre«-Programm und Gleichstellungsrates der Universität Konstanz  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 4aCrossdressing. 4aDon Giovanni. 4aGender Studies. 4aGeschlecht. 4aKinder- und Jugendliteratur. 4aKultur. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aKunst. 4aKörper. 4aLiteratur. 4aMaskerade. 4aMedien. 4aMode. 4aNiklaus Flütsch. 4aQueer Theory. 4aVirginia Woolf. 4aWilliam Shakespeare. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh  aArt.  aBody.  aChildren's and Youth Literature.  aCrossdressing.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aDon Giovanni.  aFashion Studies.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aLiterature.  aMaskerade.  aMedia.  aQueer Theory.  aTheatre.  aVirginia Woolf.  aWilliam Shakespeare.1 aBaur, Gabriel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBinswanger, Christa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöhm, Kerstin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEnderwitz, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGramatzki, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLachmund, Anne-Marie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaihofer, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRothstein, Anne-Berenike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRothstein, Anne-Berenike, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchrader, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchwan, Tanja, econtributor.4ctb4https